    <note type="dates"><date>1813–93</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>American music critic. Graduated from Harvard College, 1832; Harvard Divinity School, 1836. His views on music were based on a combination of associationist philosophy and transcendentalism. Founded <hi rend="italic">Dwight’s Journal of Music</hi> in 1852; sole editor until 1881.</p></note>
